    narr:generatedFrom "d1b09a828565de86" ;
    narr:narration """This hub gathers the product's tool surface and capability decisions, mostly dated March–May 2026. The dominant arc is aggressive consolidation: a March–April sweep settled the [five user-facing MCP tools](narr:Claim_FiveCoreMCPTools) — perspective, cite, introspect, remember, review — while [refract and its registry](narr:Claim_RefractRegistryRemovedFromProduct), the [memories/source tool](narr:Claim_MemoriesSourceToolRemoved), [discoveries](narr:Claim_RemoveDiscoveries), the [notifications system](narr:Claim_RemoveNotificationsSystem), and [auto-generated TX summaries](narr:Claim_TXSummariesAutoGenRemoved) were removed; scope and lens folded inward. The [review tool was widened to three cases](narr:Claim_ReviewToolThreeCases). Capability framing runs alongside: [compilation layers](narr:Obs_CompilationLayers) from 4K bootstrap to 100K expansion, [perspective layering](narr:Obs_ChineseHerbalismLayeringExample), [transcript bootstrapping](narr:Claim_TranscriptBootstrapOnramp) as a lighter onramp, and a [public perspective module](narr:Narrative_PublicPerspectiveModule). Against the removal current, the [Feedback/Help tool](narr:Claim_FeedbackHelpAboveLine) was pulled *above* the line as primary churn prevention. Early usage (May) showed [two organic loop patterns](narr:Claim_FourToolLoopEngagedUserPattern) across the enterprise customer's first nine days.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_CompileRename> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_FeedbackHelpAboveLine> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_FiveCoreMCPTools> ;
